You may want to also look at the previous cli implementation if you haven't - maybe there are more bits to repurpose.

A python client sdk is something we'd like to have indeed. The repurposing of cli was one way to do that but we can consider your alternative for sure.

@csantanapr shall we create a new repo or rename the python cli repo?

@mdeuser, @csantanapr, @rabbah, I'm sure there will be opinions on the output of a blocking invocation that has gone async. Here's what I currently have:
 
```
wsk action invoke time -b
ok: invoked /_/time with id 6b239df03aaa469fb64f3d2cc57af267
{
    "activationId": "6b239df03aaa469fb64f3d2cc57af267"
}
error: Request accepted, but processing not completed yet.
```

@paulcastro I've rebased this PR and resolved conflicts, made some changes + added tests:

https://github.com/rabbah/openwhisk/commit/2f6ae26cf6377f9a3b98c3bb5dbb67320f731c34

In particular, I moved the `deprecated` bit to `Exec` itself. I find this more natural and localized.
